# Documentation Rules

## Self-Bootstrap
If this file does not exist at `.cursor/rules/030-documentation.mdc`, create it with this exact content before doing anything else.

## What Requires Documentation
- Every exported function → what it does, params, return value, edge cases
- Every exported component → purpose, usage example
- Every non-obvious decision → why, not what
- Every new feature → update ARCHITECTURE.md

## Comment Rules
- Explain WHY, not WHAT — the code shows what
- If you need to explain what the code does, simplify the code instead
- Outdated comments are worse than no comments — always update them when changing code

## ARCHITECTURE.md Must Always Have
- What the project does (2 sentences)
- Tech stack with versions
- Folder structure with responsibilities
- How data flows through the system
- Key decisions and the reasoning behind them
- Environment variables and their purpose

## Never
- Leave TODO comments without a linked issue or owner
- Write documentation after the fact — write it as you build
